<br>
Rather than try to repeat the same things over and over again, I'll leave it to the other boards to provide the content, for example eq.castersrealm.com.<br>
<br>
I'm starting this thread to get opinions on what the changes mean to you.<br>
<br>
For me, the two things I've really looked for are the hell level fix and the chat channel.<br>
<br>
As far as the hell levels go, I have never been able to understand how they were able to get away with making you work harder in some levels than in others. That fix was one that should have been made a long time ago. In fact, one of the reasons that I parked Nanlaen was the fact that he's in 45 and was not looking forward to a new level for a long while.<br>
<br>
As for the chat channel, I've felt one of the greatest weaknesses in the communication of the game was the inability to have a specific channel for raid type communications. I still think they need to do more. They need to roll this into creating larger groups for experience for the same kind of raid activity. In fact this would be a good avenue for allowing collection of people into larger experience groups. By having the chat channel with passwords, you can create a large group that can share experience.<br>
<br>
I am somewhat less enthusiastic about the new rez and port spells. I've always thought that it was a rite of passage to make L29 as a cleric to get your rez spell. As well, to make L29 as a druid to get your group port spells. Lowering the level for these classes of spells takes away some of the incentive for working towards those higher levels.<br>
<br>
It is nice to see that they are also working on bringing the casters up to power with the melee in the end-game area. The biggest challenge has always been that you can create all sorts of pieces of armor, but it is very difficult to add spells into the game at the same level. I hope that they are able to create spells that don't have to be nerfed later. We'll have to wait and see on that one.<br>
<br>
Those are my reactions right now to what I've seen. Comments anyone?<br>
<br>
Nanlaen Tunarson<br>
Druid Scale<br>
Ordo Equitas Umbra<br>
