o could rez me sure would've been nice and made my $10 a month a little more worth the fun and less worth the aggrevation.  I agree that it's a bit of a let-down that you don't have to work as hard to get to that level where resurrections are possible, but I sincerely doubt that people will work any less hard for higher levels now that they can do these things earlier...right now I'm trying to get to 53rd level just so I can get to 53rd level.<br>
<br>
Also...the desirability of Clerics in low levels is practically non-existant.  Druids and Shaman get healing spells that are definitely on par with Clerics until 24+ plus they get better aggressive spells *and* SoW.  Most groups below 24 and sometimes even above that level when looking for a healer will pick a Druid over a Cleric 9 times out of 10 because of these reasons.  With these new resurrection spells it makes the choice much harder indeed!  Clerics now are just as desirable (if you ask me) as a Druid is at these levels and it evens the playing field for them a lot.  Of course Clerics don't have these problems at higher levels but in the lower levels it can be pretty difficult for them, and thus many people who start Clerics don't really go far with them because when starting out they're not very desirable and they can't solo to get that experience.  I think this change might even mean more Clerics in the world both at higher levels and at lower levels.<br>
<br>
